	$LF
]h2
[hr 
]hr
[p 
	[del 
		"This guide is intended to be a detailed walkthrough of our standard approach for creating the high quality multimedia files published alongside our movies from the input files that are normally submitted to the site.  Following this guide is the easiest way to meet the 
		(__wikiLink|/EncoderGuidelines|Encoder Guidelines)
		" (which you should review before and during the process this guide outlines).
		$LF
	]del
]p
[p 
	"Please note that this guide is intended for 
	[b 
		"encodes intended to be published
	]b
	", i.e. those that are available through mirrors and BitTorrent.  There are some differences in the process when uploading to 
	(__wikiLink|/Streamingmedia|streaming media)
	" sites; for some of those differences, consult 
	(__wikiLink|/EncodingGuide/StreamingMedia|Encoding Guide/Streaming Media)
	".
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"We are always on the lookout for new encoders, to create encodes for movies presently in the 
	[a class=intlink href=/Subs-List 
		"submission queue
	]a
	".  If you want to help out, read on!
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The guide has been laid out in the following six steps:
	$LF
]p
[ol 
	[li 
		" 
		[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/Requirements 
			"Requirements
		]a
		" - what you need before you get started.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/Logo 
			"Logo
		]a
		" - creating your distinctive encoder logo which identifies an encode as yours.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/VideoDumping 
			"Video Dumping
		]a
		" - setting up the emulator to record video from the input file.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/PreEncoding 
			"Pre-encoding
		]a
		" - putting together the logo, subtitles, and video dump in preparation for encoding.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/Encoding 
			"Encoding
		]a
		" - what it's all about!
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/Packaging 
			"Packaging
		]a
		" - muxing your encoded streams and what to do with your encode once it is done.
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[p 
	"There's also an all-in-one package available and developed along with the 
	[a class=intlink href=/EncodingGuide/HybridEncodeScript 
		"Hybrid Encode Script
	]a
	". Currently it's the only mantained page of the guide, check it regularly.
	[del 
		$LF
	]del
]p
[p 
	"If you have questions about the process, you can either:
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" visit our 
		[a class=intlink href=/Forum/F/52 
			"Encoders' Corner
		]a
		" forum, intended for discussion between our new and veteran encoders alike; or
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" contact one of our present 
		[a class=intlink href=/Users 
			"publishers
		]a
		" or 
		(__wikiLink|/Encoders|encoders)
		", either by forum PM or by 
		[a class=intlink href=/IRCChannel 
			"IRC
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"Good luck!
